    • Method Detail

      • createData

        public void createData(Map<String,Object> params,
              ISirqulCallback<ObjectStoreResponse> callback)
        Create a record for the specified object. If the object does not exist then a new one will be created prior to inserting the record. If any of the fields included does not exist for the object then they are added to the object.

        The data type for the new fields are inferred from the JSON type, they are:

        • DATE -> quoted string of the format: yyyy-MM-dd hh:mm:ss
        • STRING -> quoted string of any format except a date
        • NUMBER -> unquoted number
        • BOOLEAN -> unquoted string of the format: true or false

        The data structure is: 

         
 {
        "stringField":"value",
        "dateField":"2014-01-01 00:00:00",
        "numberField":23.98,
        "booleanField":true
 }


        Target API Endpoint: /object/data/create

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account id of the logged in user
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          The application key for updating an existing application
        • SirqulKeys.objectName
          The name of the object to add data to
        • SirqulKeys.data
          The content to add, structured JSON

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        ObjectStoreResponse
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - the callback
        See Also:
        ObjectStoreApiBase.createData(...)

      • searchData

        public void searchData(Map<String,Object> params,
              ISirqulCallback<ObjectStoreResponse> callback)
        Search for records given the specified criteria. The criteria is a defined set of json values used to build a query. The search criteria structure is: 
         
 {
        "field1":
        {
                "operation1":"value1",
                "operation2":"value2"
        },
        "field2":
        {
                "operation3":["value3","value4"]
        }
 }
        The supported operations are:
        • eq -> equal to
        • neq -> not equal to
        • lt -> less than
        • lte -> less than or equal to
        • gt -> greater than
        • gte -> greater than or equal to
        • in -> contained in (array)
        • nin -> not contained in (array)
        • exist -> true: some value set, false: no value set (null)

        This example will find any record with a score between 500 and 5000 that was updated any time after Jan 1, 2014 and is for a player named Bob or Ben: 

         
 {
        "score":{"gte":500, "lte":5000},
        "updated":{"gte":"2014-01-01 00:00:00"},
        "playerName":"{"in":["Bob","Ben"]}
 }

        All operations across all fields are AND clauses.

        Target API Endpoint: /object/data/search

        Available parameters for this api

        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account id of the logged in user
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          The application key for updating an existing application
        • SirqulKeys.objectName
          The name of the object to search upon
        • SirqulKeys.criteria
          The search criteria
        • SirqulKeys.count
          If true just return the record count of the search. False (default) will return the actual records
        • SirqulKeys.start
          The start of the pagination
        • SirqulKeys.limit
          The limit of the pagination
        • SirqulKeys.order
          The order of results; comma separated list of field names. Illegal field names will be ignored. Direction by default is ascending. Prepend a minus to the field name to make that field descending.

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        ObjectStoreResponse
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - the callback
        See Also:
        ObjectStoreApiBase.searchData(...)

      • updateData

        public void updateData(Map<String,Object> params,
              ISirqulCallback<ObjectStoreResponse> callback)
        Update a record for the specified object. If the object does not exist the request will be rejected, use the data create service for the first entry. If any of the fields included does not exist for the object then they are added to the object.

        See the data create service for the structured data format.

        Target API Endpoint: /object/data/update

        Available parameters for this api

        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account id of the logged in user
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          The application key for updating an existing application
        • SirqulKeys.objectName
          The name of the object to add data to
        • SirqulKeys.objectId
          objectId The id of the record to update
        • SirqulKeys.data
          The content to update, structured JSON
